race.comment: Interesting way to start the day and the recent Melbourne Cup winners look to have a smart filly on their hands in GOD ONLY KNOWS (12). Has looked strong winning two recent jumpouts, one at Ballarat and another at Flemington, when there looked to be plenty left in the tank. Looks to have the racing style that will be able to take full advantage of the low draw. WINTER HAIL (7) missed the frame when resuming last start over 1000m at Bendigo but wasn't all that far from the winner. Won't find this as tough. Sure to go well. BRENLYN'S LEGACY (4) has been primed for a good return after placing in two trials leading into this. Rates highly and bold showing expected. WINGSANDPROPELLERS (3) gave a sight on debut, when not beaten far, and should be thereabouts again. KGALAGADI (5) is on debut and has been well held in his past two jumpouts, but went to the line with plenty in hand and gets the blinkers here.
